---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="proof"
  description="n0brains live forward-return proof — every signal type measured against real post-signal price action, with win rate, excess over buy-and-hold, and confidence intervals. The exact gate we use to flag signals. Not advice."
>
  <section class="about-section">
    <h1>proof</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">
      We measure <strong>every directional signal</strong> against real
      post-signal price action — Hyperliquid 1-hour candles — at the 24h horizon
      over a rolling 30-day window. For each signal type we publish the win rate,
      the mean return of the trade itself, the mean <strong>excess over simply
      buying and holding</strong>, and 95% confidence intervals. A type is marked
      <strong>proven</strong> only when it clears 30+ measured signals AND both
      beats buy-and-hold AND is profitable on its own (excess-return CI lower
      bound above zero). This is the <em>exact</em> gate the pipeline uses to flag
      <code>conviction: strong</code> — so this page can never claim edge the
      product doesn't actually act on. Refreshed live.
    </p>

    <div id="proof-banner" class="proof-banner proof-loading">
      <span class="dot"></span>
      <span class="banner-text">loading results…</span>
    </div>

    <div id="proof-table"></div>

    <p class="meta" id="proof-meta"></p>

    <h2 class="tier-heading">Edge accumulation</h2>
    <p class="tier-blurb">
      Does the per-signal edge above actually compound, or is it a few lucky
      outliers? Below is an illustrative account starting at index 100 that takes
      <strong>every proven-type signal</strong>, one at a time, risking
      <span id="eq-alloc">1%</span> of equity per signal and compounding the
      realized 24h return — in fire-time order. Fixed fractional size, no
      leverage, no stacking. <strong>Illustrative of edge accumulation on measured
      returns, not a live-traded or guaranteed account.</strong>
    </p>
    <div id="equity-wrap">
      <div id="equity-legend" class="equity-legend"></div>
      <div id="equity-chart" class="equity-chart">loading…</div>
    </div>
    <p class="meta" id="equity-meta"></p>

    <h2 class="tier-heading">Risk-tier performance</h2>
    <p class="tier-blurb">
      The same signals can be run with different stop-loss, take-profit, and
      sizing rules depending on how aggressive you want to be. Below are the
      paper-traded results for three reference tiers — conservative (1),
      balanced (2), and aggressive (3) — over the last 30 days. Source:
      <code>/performance?tier=N</code>. Each tier filters the strategy set
      AND scales SL/TP/size from a base config.
    </p>

    <div id="tier-cards" class="tier-cards">
      <div class="tier-card" data-tier="1">
        <h3>1 · Conservative</h3>
        <div class="tier-body">loading…</div>
      </div>
      <div class="tier-card" data-tier="2">
        <h3>2 · Balanced</h3>
        <div class="tier-body">loading…</div>
      </div>
      <div class="tier-card" data-tier="3">
        <h3>3 · Aggressive</h3>
        <div class="tier-body">loading…</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="meta" id="tier-meta"></p>

    <p class="legal-updated" style="margin-top: 32px;">
      A type is shown as <strong>forward-return proven</strong> only when its
      live post-signal price record clears 30+ measured signals AND both beats
      buy-and-hold and is profitable on its own, with a 95% confidence interval
      above zero. (Beating buy-and-hold alone isn't enough — a type that only
      looks good by being short in a downtrend, while still losing money, does
      not qualify.) These are the types we flag <code>conviction: strong</code>
      in the API. Measured on real prices for informational purposes only — not
      financial advice, and past performance does not guarantee future results.
      See <a href="/terms">terms</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const ENDPOINT = "https://api.n0brains.com/proof";

  function pct(v) {
    if (v === null || v === undefined) return "—";
    const n = Number(v) * 100;
    return n.toFixed(1) + "%";
  }
  function pctRaw(v) {
    if (v === null || v === undefined) return "—";
    return (Number(v) >= 0 ? "+" : "") + Number(v).toFixed(2) + "%";
  }
  function usd(v) {
    if (v === null || v === undefined) return "—";
    const n = Number(v);
    return (n >= 0 ? "+$" : "-$") + Math.abs(n).toFixed(2);
  }

  function render(data) {
    const banner = document.getElementById("proof-banner");
    const table  = document.getElementById("proof-table");
    const meta   = document.getElementById("proof-meta");

    if (!data || data.error || !data.types) {
      banner.className = "proof-banner proof-unknown";
      banner.querySelector(".banner-text").textContent =
        "proof unavailable (" + (data?.error || "fetch failed") + ")";
      return;
    }

    const tradeable = data.types.filter((t) => t.tradeable);
    banner.className = "proof-banner proof-up";
    banner.querySelector(".banner-text").textContent =
      tradeable.length + " signal type" + (tradeable.length === 1 ? "" : "s") +
      " forward-return proven";

    let rows = "";
    for (const t of data.types) {
      const cls = t.tradeable ? "row-tradeable" : "row-untradeable";
      const flag = t.tradeable
        ? '<span class="badge badge-yes">proven</span>'
        : '<span class="badge badge-no">intel only</span>';
      // CI shown as the lower bound on excess return — the conservative edge.
      const ciCls = t.ci_low_pct > 0 ? "pos" : "neg";
      rows += `
        <tr class="${cls}">
          <td class="type">${t.signal_type}</td>
          <td>${t.n}</td>
          <td>${pct(t.win_rate)}</td>
          <td class="${t.avg_net_pct >= 0 ? "pos" : "neg"}">${pctRaw(t.avg_net_pct)}</td>
          <td class="${t.excess_pct >= 0 ? "pos" : "neg"}">${pctRaw(t.excess_pct)}</td>
          <td class="${ciCls}">${pctRaw(t.ci_low_pct)}</td>
          <td>${flag}</td>
        </tr>`;
    }
    table.innerHTML = `
      <table class="proof-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>type</th><th>signals</th><th>win rate</th>
              <th title="mean return of the trade itself">avg return</th>
              <th title="mean return minus buy-and-hold over the same window">excess vs hold</th>
              <th title="95% confidence lower bound on excess return — the conservative edge">excess CI low</th>
              <th></th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>${rows}</tbody>
      </table>`;

    if (data.types[0] && data.types[0].updated_at) {
      const latest = Math.max(...data.types.map((t) => t.updated_at || 0));
      meta.textContent = "Last updated " + new Date(latest * 1000).toISOString();
    }
  }

  async function load() {
    try {
      const r = await fetch(ENDPOINT, { cache: "no-store" });
      render(await r.json());
    } catch (e) {
      render({ error: String(e) });
    }
  }

  load();
  setInterval(load, 60_000);

  // ── Equity curve (illustrative edge accumulation) ──────────────────
  const EQUITY_ENDPOINT = "https://api.n0brains.com/proof/equity";
  const TYPE_COLORS = ["#4ade80", "#60a5fa", "#f59e0b", "#c084fc", "#f472b6"];

  function buildPath(points, x0, y0, w, h, tMin, tMax, eqMin, eqMax) {
    if (!points.length) return "";
    const sx = (t) => x0 + ((t - tMin) / (tMax - tMin || 1)) * w;
    const sy = (e) => y0 + h - ((e - eqMin) / (eqMax - eqMin || 1)) * h;
    // Downsample to ~300 points so the SVG path stays light.
    const step = Math.max(1, Math.floor(points.length / 300));
    let d = "";
    for (let i = 0; i < points.length; i += step) {
      const p = points[i];
      d += (d ? "L" : "M") + sx(p.t).toFixed(1) + "," + sy(p.equity).toFixed(1) + " ";
    }
    const last = points[points.length - 1];
    d += "L" + sx(last.t).toFixed(1) + "," + sy(last.equity).toFixed(1);
    return d;
  }

  function renderEquity(d) {
    const chart = document.getElementById("equity-chart");
    const legend = document.getElementById("equity-legend");
    const meta = document.getElementById("equity-meta");
    const allocEl = document.getElementById("eq-alloc");
    if (!d || d.error || !d.combined || !d.combined.length) {
      chart.innerHTML = "<div class='tier-err'>equity curve unavailable</div>";
      return;
    }
    if (allocEl && d.alloc_frac_per_signal != null) {
      allocEl.textContent = (d.alloc_frac_per_signal * 100).toFixed(d.alloc_frac_per_signal < 0.01 ? 1 : 0) + "%";
    }

    const W = 720, H = 300, padL = 48, padR = 16, padT = 16, padB = 28;
    const w = W - padL - padR, h = H - padT - padB;

    // Series: combined + each proven type. "All proven" gets a bright, thick
    // white line so it reads as the headline series vs the thinner per-type lines.
    const COMBINED_COLOR = "#ffffff";
    const series = [{ name: "All proven (combined)", points: d.combined, color: COMBINED_COLOR, width: 2.6 }];
    const types = Object.keys(d.by_type || {});
    types.forEach((t, i) => {
      series.push({ name: t, points: d.by_type[t], color: TYPE_COLORS[i % TYPE_COLORS.length], width: 1.6 });
    });

    let tMin = Infinity, tMax = -Infinity, eqMin = Infinity, eqMax = -Infinity;
    for (const s of series) for (const p of s.points) {
      if (p.t < tMin) tMin = p.t; if (p.t > tMax) tMax = p.t;
      if (p.equity < eqMin) eqMin = p.equity; if (p.equity > eqMax) eqMax = p.equity;
    }
    // Pad the y-range a touch and always include the 100 baseline.
    eqMin = Math.min(eqMin, 100); eqMax = Math.max(eqMax, 100);
    const yPad = (eqMax - eqMin) * 0.08 || 1; eqMin -= yPad; eqMax += yPad;

    const yBase = padT + h - ((100 - eqMin) / (eqMax - eqMin || 1)) * h;
    const gridVals = [eqMin, (eqMin + eqMax) / 2, eqMax];
    let grid = "";
    for (const gv of gridVals) {
      const gy = padT + h - ((gv - eqMin) / (eqMax - eqMin || 1)) * h;
      grid += `<line x1="${padL}" y1="${gy.toFixed(1)}" x2="${W - padR}" y2="${gy.toFixed(1)}" class="eq-grid"/>`;
      grid += `<text x="${padL - 6}" y="${(gy + 3).toFixed(1)}" class="eq-axis" text-anchor="end">${gv.toFixed(0)}</text>`;
    }

    let paths = "";
    for (const s of series) {
      const dPath = buildPath(s.points, padL, padT, w, h, tMin, tMax, eqMin, eqMax);
      paths += `<path d="${dPath}" fill="none" stroke="${s.color}" stroke-width="${s.width}"/>`;
    }

    chart.innerHTML = `
      <svg viewBox="0 0 ${W} ${H}" class="eq-svg" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
        ${grid}
        <line x1="${padL}" y1="${yBase.toFixed(1)}" x2="${W - padR}" y2="${yBase.toFixed(1)}" class="eq-base"/>
        ${paths}
      </svg>`;

    // Legend built straight from `series` so colors + labels always match the
    // chart lines exactly. Swatch is a short line segment (matching the drawn
    // line), not a square, so "this color = this line" is unambiguous. Each
    // entry shows the series' final return.
    const byRet = d.by_type_return_pct || {};
    const retFor = (s) => s.name.startsWith("All proven")
      ? d.combined_return_pct
      : byRet[s.name];
    legend.innerHTML =
      `<span class="eq-leg-title">Lines</span>` +
      series.map((s) => {
        const r = retFor(s);
        const rv = (r === null || r === undefined) ? "" :
          `<b class="${r >= 0 ? "pos" : "neg"}">${pctRaw(r)}</b>`;
        // Fully inline the swatch styles: this span is injected via innerHTML, so
        // Astro's SCOPED CSS (.eq-swatch[data-astro-cid-…]) never matches it —
        // the dimensions/border must live on the element itself, not in <style>.
        const sw = `display:inline-block;width:14px;height:14px;border-radius:3px;`
          + `flex:0 0 auto;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.25);background:${s.color};`;
        return `<span class="eq-leg-item">` +
          `<span class="eq-swatch" style="${sw}"></span>` +
          `<span class="eq-leg-name">${s.name}</span>${rv}</span>`;
      }).join("");

    if (meta) {
      meta.textContent =
        `${d.n_signals} proven signals over ${d.window_days} days (~${d.signals_per_day}/day) · ` +
        `index 100 → ${d.combined_final_index} · ${d.alloc_frac_per_signal != null ? (d.alloc_frac_per_signal * 100).toFixed(d.alloc_frac_per_signal < 0.01 ? 1 : 0) + "% per signal" : ""} · ` +
        `illustrative, not a live account`;
    }
  }

  async function loadEquity() {
    try {
      const r = await fetch(EQUITY_ENDPOINT, { cache: "no-store" });
      renderEquity(await r.json());
    } catch (e) {
      renderEquity({ error: String(e) });
    }
  }
  loadEquity();
  setInterval(loadEquity, 120_000);

  // Risk-tier performance — fetch /performance?tier=N for N in {1,2,3}.
  const TIER_LABELS = { 1: "Conservative", 2: "Balanced", 3: "Aggressive" };

  function renderTier(tier, data) {
    const card = document.querySelector(`.tier-card[data-tier="${tier}"] .tier-body`);
    if (!card) return;
    const tp = data && data.tier_performance;
    if (!tp) {
      card.innerHTML = "<div class='tier-err'>no data</div>";
      return;
    }
    const totalCls = tp.total_pnl_usd >= 0 ? "pos" : "neg";
    const sharpe = tp.sharpe === null || tp.sharpe === undefined
      ? "—"
      : Number(tp.sharpe).toFixed(2);
    const contributors = (tp.top_contributors || []).join(", ") || "—";
    let strategyRows = "";
    const byStrat = tp.by_strategy || {};
    for (const [name, s] of Object.entries(byStrat)) {
      const pnlCls = s.total_pnl_usd >= 0 ? "pos" : "neg";
      strategyRows += `
        <tr>
          <td>${name}</td>
          <td>${s.n}</td>
          <td>${Number(s.win_pct).toFixed(1)}%</td>
          <td class="${pnlCls}">${usd(s.total_pnl_usd)}</td>
          <td>${s.sharpe === null || s.sharpe === undefined ? "—" : Number(s.sharpe).toFixed(2)}</td>
        </tr>`;
    }
    card.innerHTML = `
      <div class="tier-summary">
        <div><span class="muted">n</span> ${tp.n}</div>
        <div><span class="muted">win</span> ${Number(tp.win_pct).toFixed(1)}%</div>
        <div><span class="muted">total</span> <span class="${totalCls}">${usd(tp.total_pnl_usd)}</span></div>
        <div><span class="muted">sharpe</span> ${sharpe}</div>
      </div>
      <table class="tier-table">
        <thead><tr><th>strategy</th><th>n</th><th>win</th><th>PnL</th><th>sharpe</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>${strategyRows || "<tr><td colspan='5' class='muted'>none qualifying</td></tr>"}</tbody>
      </table>
      <div class="tier-foot muted">top: ${contributors}</div>
    `;
  }

  async function loadTier(tier) {
    try {
      const r = await fetch(
        `https://api.n0brains.com/performance?days=30&tier=${tier}`,
        { cache: "no-store" }
      );
      renderTier(tier, await r.json());
    } catch (e) {
      const card = document.querySelector(`.tier-card[data-tier="${tier}"] .tier-body`);
      if (card) card.innerHTML = `<div class="tier-err">load failed: ${e}</div>`;
    }
  }

  async function loadAllTiers() {
    await Promise.all([loadTier(1), loadTier(2), loadTier(3)]);
    const meta = document.getElementById("tier-meta");
    if (meta) {
      try {
        const r = await fetch(
          "https://api.n0brains.com/performance?days=30&tier=1",
          { cache: "no-store" }
        );
        const d = await r.json();
        if (d?.tier_performance?.generated_at) {
          meta.textContent =
            "tier rollup generated " + d.tier_performance.generated_at +
            " · " + (d.tier_performance.methodology || "");
        }
      } catch {}
    }
  }
  loadAllTiers();
  setInterval(loadAllTiers, 60_000);
</script>

<style>
  .proof-banner {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px;
    padding: 16px 20px; border-radius: 6px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem; border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .proof-banner .dot {
    width: 10px; height: 10px; border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--text-muted);
  }
  .proof-up { border-color: #2a7a2a; }
  .proof-up .dot { background: #4ade80; box-shadow: 0 0 6px #4ade80; }
  .proof-unknown { border-color: var(--border); }
  .proof-loading .dot { background: var(--accent); }

  .proof-table {
    width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.88rem;
  }
  .proof-table th, .proof-table td {
    padding: 10px 12px; text-align: left;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .proof-table th { color: var(--text-muted); font-weight: 500; }
  .proof-table td.type { font-weight: 600; }
  .proof-table .pos { color: #4ade80; }
  .proof-table .neg { color: #ef4444; }
  .row-untradeable { opacity: 0.55; }

  .badge {
    font-size: 0.72rem; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 10px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .badge-yes { color: #4ade80; border-color: #2a7a2a; }
  .badge-no  { color: var(--text-muted); }

  .meta { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.8rem; margin-top: 1rem;
          font-family: var(--font-mono); }

  .tier-heading { margin-top: 2.5rem; }
  .tier-blurb { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .tier-cards {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem; margin-top: 1rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .tier-cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .tier-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1rem 1.1rem; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }
  .tier-card h3 { margin: 0 0 0.6rem; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .tier-summary {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 4px 8px; font-size: 0.82rem; margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }
  .tier-summary .muted { color: var(--text-muted); margin-right: 4px; }
  .tier-table {
    width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.78rem;
    margin-top: 0.3rem;
  }
  .tier-table th, .tier-table td {
    padding: 6px 6px; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .tier-table th { color: var(--text-muted); font-weight: 500; }
  .tier-table .pos { color: #4ade80; }
  .tier-table .neg { color: #ef4444; }
  .tier-foot { font-size: 0.75rem; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
  .tier-err { color: #ef4444; font-size: 0.8rem; }

  /* Equity curve */
  #equity-wrap {
    border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1rem 1.1rem 0.6rem; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
  .equity-chart { width: 100%; }
  /* SVG injected via chart.innerHTML -> :global (scoped selectors miss it). */
  :global(.eq-svg) { width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }
  :global(.eq-grid) { stroke: var(--border); stroke-width: 1; opacity: 0.35; }
  :global(.eq-base) { stroke: var(--text-muted); stroke-width: 1; stroke-dasharray: 3 3; opacity: 0.6; }
  :global(.eq-axis) { fill: var(--text-muted); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; }
  .equity-legend {
    display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; gap: 8px 18px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.82rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem; padding-bottom: 0.7rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  /* These elements are injected via innerHTML at runtime, so they must be
     styled with :global() — Astro's default scoped selectors (which add a
     data-astro-cid attribute) never match JS-created nodes. Swatch size/color
     is also inlined in the JS as a belt-and-suspenders. */
  :global(.eq-leg-title) { color: var(--text-muted); text-transform: uppercase;
    font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.06em; margin-right: 2px; }
  :global(.eq-leg-item) { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 7px; }
  :global(.eq-swatch) { width: 14px; height: 14px; border-radius: 3px;
    display: inline-block; flex: 0 0 auto; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.25); }
  :global(.eq-leg-name) { color: var(--text); }
  :global(.equity-legend b) { font-weight: 600; }
  :global(.equity-legend .pos) { color: #4ade80; }
  :global(.equity-legend .neg) { color: #ef4444; }
</style>
